The Epic pet DS is called ElementalMasteryAura.<br>
<br>
Easy to check this now, summon until one casts it's DS, then /pet health, and check the buff list.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=927&amp;source=Live">FireElementalAura</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (Increase Damage Shield by 3 (L1) to 62 (L60) &amp; Increase Fire Resist by 5).<br>
<br>
The highest DS a Magician can cast on their pet is the level 56 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1667&amp;source=Live">Cadeau of Flame</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, which is 33pts.  This means that once your pet is level 32 or higher, it will have a superior DS and and your DS spell will not land.  Monster Summoning III pets should be in the high 40s.<br>
<br>
All pets these days tend to DS themselves within the first 30 seconds.  The longest I've had to wait is a couple of minutes.<br>
<br>
As for how frequently you will get a MS pet that casts a DS, no idea.  I have rarely used MS3 (epic equipped).  Just buy a bag full of malochite, and spend some time summoning.  100 or so pets should be enough to give you semi accurate numbers. <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
